title: For Sale:  Ruger Blackhawk 3 screw .357 Magnum
postcontent: Ruger Blackhawk 3 screw .357 Magnum with a 4 5/8” barrel and in excellent shape. The old models, called a 3 screw were made from 1963 to 1973 and this one was made in 1972.  Fully adjustable rear sight, and hardwood grips. The action typical of an old model is very smooth with a great trigger pull, something you don’t find in a new model. The feel of the old model in both size and action is exactly like a colt single action but it is much more reliable. It was not sent back to the factory to have the transfer bar conversion installed. So if you carried it in a holster it should be loaded with 5 round and an empty chamber under the hammer. The bluing very good shape with no drag lines on the cylinder or holster wear on barrel or cylinder. . $450 Cash firm  Mac REDACTED

title: For Sale/Trade:  Llama Omni III 9MM W/Leather Holster
postcontent:
Excellent condition Llama Omni III 9mm cal. With a 13rd factory magazine. All steel, well built gun. Blued finish, and has a safety-decocker feature. Single and double action semi-auto pistol. Made in Spain & imported by Stoeger Arms Company of New Jersey. Has a 4-1/2" barrel, square notch drift windage adjustable rear sight, fixed front post sight - Serrated Hammer Spur - Smooth Combat Trigger - Combat Style Front Trigger Guard - Side Lever Safety Latch - Side Slide Release Latch - Side Magazine Release Button. It comes with a DeSantis black leather holster. This gun is in excellent plus condition for its age (the Omnis were imported back in the early 80's to the mid-80's) This gun is kind of a rare oddity since they were just imported in the U.S. for a very short period of time. It has some very unique features in the gun for a Llama. You must be at least 21 years or older, and a Kentucky resident with a valid Kentucky driver's license (KY CCDW okay) to purchase/trade this gun. Just email me with any questions. I can send/email some more close up pics (I can only upload 3 pictures on here). Thanks for looking. 

* $350 obo, or trade *

Below is an excerpt from one of the gun writers (from Guns & Ammo I believe) about the Llama Omni III 9mm pistol back in the early 1980's.

"Back in 1982 - Llama introduced the "ultimate" 9mm/.45 series of pistols - the Llama Omni, it had micro ball bearings integrated into the slide so it would not wear when it cycled against the frame, along with some new innovative features for a semi-automatic pistol. This was the most original and sophisticated Llama ever designed, incorporating such unique features as ball bearings for the hammer pivot, separate drawbars for the single and double action sears, a deeply undercut trigger guard to allow high hand positioning for recoil control, a 13-round double stack magazine that tapered to a single column at the top  and "buttressed" rifling, which used a 2-stage "step-down" from the lands to the grooves, for less bullet deformation and a better gas seal  Most of these features have never been found all together in any other single design, and provide this pistol with an extremely smooth and reliable action."

Treated Barrel (Weapon Armament Surface Protection) is a salt bath ferritic nitrocarburizing surface conversion process or more commonly referred to as nitriding. The nitriding conversion is applied to the barrel inside and out, along with the front sight base on our LE rifles and uppers. Nitriding offers improved wear, abrasion, and corrosion resistance when compared to hard chrome lining or phosphating. Unlike chrome lining, where the chrome is built up on the surface, nitriding converts the surface without the risk of dimensional build up.
